% Google Gemini / Antigravity CLI profile for a Claude-Code-/simplify-equivalent cleanup pass.
% Reference-only today: `pdd checkup simplify` does not invoke Gemini yet.

<include>checkup_simplify_workflow_LLM.prompt</include>

<gemini>
## Prerequisites
- `gemini` or `agy` CLI on PATH (PDD discovers both via `agentic_common`).
- Valid Google/Gemini credentials per your installation (API key or OAuth).

## Suggested invocation pattern (manual / future PDD wiring)
Legacy Gemini CLI example inside the candidate worktree:

```bash
cd "$CANDIDATE_WORKTREE"
printf '%s\n' "Simplify only these files: pdd/foo.py pdd/bar.py" \
  | gemini --yolo --output-format json
```

Antigravity (`agy`) builds may prefer piping the full workflow prompt on stdin:

```bash
cd "$CANDIDATE_WORKTREE"
agy --dangerously-skip-permissions --print < /path/to/simplify_prompt.txt
```

## Model selection
- `GEMINI_MODEL` may be documented for future wiring; many Gemini CLI builds ignore model flags.
- Treat stdout as the agent summary; parse JSON only when the CLI actually emits JSON.

## Parity notes
- Scope, conservatism, and verification expectations are identical to Claude simplify.
- PDD verification (`ruff`, `mypy`, `pytest`) still runs in the candidate worktree after the agent pass.
</gemini>
